text: Vic Carroll (30 April 1912 – 18 October 1998) was an Australian rules footballer who played 12 consecutive games with Fitzroy in 1937 in the Victorian Football League (VFL). Carroll made his debut against Geelong Football Club in round seven. Carroll was cleared back to the Corowa Football Club in the Ovens and Murray Football League in April, 1938. Carroll and his brother Norm had previously trained with the Melbourne Football Club in 1931. == Notes == == External links == * * Category:1912 births Category:1998 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from New South Wales Category:Fitzroy Football Club players Category:Corowa Football Club players
